Duck & Bacon Hot Dog (caramelized onions & sweet peppers) - I would have never known that duck and bacon would go so well together.  I was afraid it would be too oily since duck is on the oiler side, but it was perfect.  The sausage was bursting with flavors and paired with the sweet peppers and caramelized onions , it was absolutely scrumptious.  For once I finished my actual entree sooner than the fries, and I'm a big fries lover!

Food was great! Service was awful! Went for my anniversary. First they lied and said we needed a reservation to eat on the street during a pandemic on a weekday. Then she forgot my husband's drink and brought us one bottle of water to share on our anniversary. Forgot our bread. The food was amazing, salads big enough to share with table,  entrees good portion for price. Comfortable seating considering its covid and we have to eat in the street. They gave us blankets, but I recommend a sweater and light coat if your going late.

Ask for "Hachipurri" – simply put, it's a medium pizza without the tomato sauce. The cheese pie, if microwave reheated the next day, serves as breakfast! If you want a light lunch, get this dish for two, and make sure to try their Pear Soda! It's amazing. I usually buy two of these dishes otw home, and it feeds 3 people, with a quarter of one pie left over for breakfast. They also started to accept card payments! (confirmed as of 8/31/20) and the staff are very friendly.

GEORGIA 🇬🇪 Excerpt from Eat the World NYC: Grab a table or a lounge-style seat and take a look through the menu. There are no descriptions for eaters less familiar with the names of Georgian foods, so either stick to what you know or start Googling.  When the khachapuri adjaruli ($14) arrived at the table, all eyes widened and there may have been just a bit of drool forming. The bread "boat" had puffed up and risen high above its cheesy interior, possibly setting a record in New York City for tallest khachapuri.

I love this place! I live nearby. The best part about this hidden gem is that you cannot tell how beautiful it is from the street. On the street, which is nasty, it looks like a bakery. But when you walk inside and into their back yard, you walk into a different world. Music, flowers, trees. Great atmosphere, good Georgian service, low prices and the portions are HUGE. What is not to love? This place is very popular, despite being hidden. Nowadays I have to call ahead and make reservations. Very happy. This is the only trendy, delicious place to go in the neighborhood.
The food it absolutely amazing and the portions are huge. I would say this is the best traditional Georgian cousin in New York
